:\n\n  * **Supplier per-product writer**: replace any `update_processing_index(...)` with `commit_supplier_progress(...)` and show exact block.\n  * **Freeze order**: ensure `set_frozen_denominator(...)` happens **before** resume gating; provide snippet in place.\n  * **Resume gating**: demonstrate the logic (freeze → rp → slice) and show how `start_offset` is derived.\n  * **Remove off-by-one**: locate `initialize_category_processing(category_index - 1, ...)` and provide exact line diff to remove `- 1`.\n  * **Completion method**: change `mark_category_complete(...)` → `mark_category_completed(category_url)`.\n  * **Amazon commits**: confirm/patch `total_cats=1` at every `commit_amazon_progress(...)`.\n  * **Phase detection**: if wording not file-grounded, patch the diagnostic lines to read counts from the actual files; include the exact logging change (we expect `(lm_file: N, cache_file: M)`).\n  * **(If needed)** Swap any early `init` calls for a **single “entry commit”** with `prod_idx=0`, after freeze and before extraction.\n\n  ### 5) Test Protocol (repeatable)\n\n  * **Scenario A: fresh run with categories that have work**\n\n    * Expect `FROZEN DENOMINATOR` then `commit_supplier_progress` per item, `✅ RESUME HONORED` when resuming mid-cat.\n  * **Scenario B: category with zero work**\n\n    * Expect no product commits; do **not** regress the pointer; correct completion bookkeeping.\n  * **Scenario C: resume mid-category**\n\n    * Kill run mid-supplier; rerun; verify slice by `start_offset` and no double processing.\n  * **Scenario D: Amazon-only queue**\n\n    * Confirm `total_cats=1` everywhere; pointer increments via `commit_amazon_progress`.\n\n  ### 6) Acceptance Criteria (automatable via grep)\n\n  * `rg -n \"update_processing_index\\\\(\"` → **0 hits**\n  * `rg -n \"initialize_category_processing\\\\(category_index=.*- 1\"` → **0 hits**\n  * `rg -n \"commit_supplier_progress\\\\(\"` → shows supplier loop and progress callback sites\n  * `rg -n \"commit_amazon_progress\\\\(.*total_cats=1\"` → all Amazon callsites\n  * Logs show `🔒 FROZEN DENOMINATOR` **before** any resume gating for that category\n  * Logs show **no** `📋 Resume skip: category X < Y` immediately after a `NEEDS_FULL_EXTRACTION/AMAZON_ONLY` > 0\n  * State snapshots across runs show **monotonic** progress (no zeroing at run start unless truly at category 0 with no work)\n\n  ---\n\n  ## 📌 Notes & Non-Negotiables\n\n  * **Do NOT** re-introduce any resume-pointer resets at category init; pointer advancement must remain owned by the **atomic commit** calls.\n  * **Keep** resume proof banners (we use them to audit).\n  * If you find additional blocking issues (e.g., early `continue` still present), include them in Findings with precise code locations and diffs.\n\n  ---\n\n  ## 🧭 Output Format\n\n  1. **Executive Summary**\n  2. **Detailed Findings (with file\\:line evidence)**\n  3. **Root-Cause Map**\n  4. **Patch Set (diffs/snippets & exact insertion points)**\n  5. **Test Protocol & Acceptance Criteria**\n  6. **Risk/rollback notes** (how to back out if a diff causes side-effects)\n\n  ---","images":[]},{"ts":1757953850593,"type":"say","say":"api_req_started","text":"{\"request\":\"<task>\\n**Mission**: With the **same attachments** I just provided (latest scripts, 3 newest logs, and 5 processing-state snapshots), perform a full audit to determine **what of the mainplan.md ( in root folder)\\n  integrated, what’s missing, what regressed**, and why the system **skips product extraction after the 2-step filter** and **zeros category indices across runs**. Produce a surgical\\n  implementation plan with diffs and a test protocol.\\n\\n  ## 📦 Inputs (use these exact files)\\n\\n  **Scripts**\\n\\n  * `/passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py`\\n  * `/fixed_enhanced_state_manager.py`\\n\\n  **Latest logs (3)**\\n\\n  * `/run_custom_poundwholesale_20250915_192612.log`\\n  * `/run_custom_poundwholesale_20250915_193138.log`\\n  * `/run_custom_poundwholesale_20250915_193648.log`\\n\\n  **Processing state snapshots (5)---
